e door requires electricity in order to open and close with ease this is something that can be shut down due to an electric failure in the event of a storm or other common power outage cause.";i:29;s:140:"When the time comes to reconnect your garage door simply pull the emergency release cord back toward the door to re-engage the spring lever.";i:30;s:117:"You can then manually move the door to the opener carriage or use the doors remote and it will connect automatically.";i:31;s:74:"You will hear a loud click when the trolley attaches back to the carriage.";i:32;s:151:"To reset the lever pull the rope toward the overhead opener unit at about a 45 degree angle until the lever moves into position as in the images below.";i:33;s:94:"At that point the trolley should reengage and lock in unless there has been some damage to it.";i:34;s:87:"By Manage My Life May 5th 2008 Comment Give your feedback by voting on answers 4 votes.";i:35;s:125:"An emergency release cord on the garage door arm opens the trolley to allow you to disengage the garage door from the opener.";i:36;s:46:"Once the power is restored to the garage door.";i:37;s:211:"Pulling the Emergency Release Cord Moving The Door Down and Up Manually Pull the Cord Towards the Garage Door Reconnecting the Opener Carriage to the Trolley The Garage Door Should Be Closed or in Down Position.";i:38;s:115:"Steps to Reconnecting Overhead Doors Make sure you disconnect the garage door opener from the overhead door itself.";i:39;s:40:"Unplug the opener from the power source.";i:40;s:84:"This is an important step in order to avoid accidents before reconnecting your door.";i:41;s:140:"When the time comes to reconnect your garage door simply pull the emergency release cord back toward the door to re-engage the spring lever.";i:42;s:117:"You can then manually move the door to the opener carriage or use the doors remote and it will connect automatically.";i:43;s:26:"Click to read full answer.";i:44;s:70:"In this manner how do you reattach an emergency pull on a garage door.";i:45;s:169:"Releasing the Garage Door You can open your garage door manually from the inside by using the emergency-release cord which hangs from your Genie mounted overhead opener.";i:46;s:153:"Pulling down on the emergency cord will release the door from the openers carriage as shown in the image above allowing you to operate the door manually.";i:47;s:126:"Garage door openers are handy appliances until something goes wrong -- then they can actually make it harder to open the door.";i:48;s:68:"The emergency release cord is there to make sure that doesnt happen.";}}